#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Advantage of a VPN for self-hosting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:7
msgid ""
"Since setting up a server at home is an uncommon practice, most Internet "
"connections provided to individuals are unsuitable for this purpose. A net "
"neutral VPN providing a static IPv4 address and IPv6 addresses can help to "
"circumvent some limitations or difficulties."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block (caution)
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Not all existing [VPN providers](/admin/get_started/providers/vpn/) meet these conditions, make sure the one you choose meets them.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Plug & Play"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:17
msgid ""
"By setting up a VPN on your server, you'll be able to make it accessible to "
"the rest of the Internet without having to change the configuration of the "
"router you connect it to. This can be really handy if you are going on "
"vacation, moving or have an Internet disconnection, as you will be able to "
"easily connect it to someone you trust without having to configure the "
"router of the person who is helping you."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:19
msgid ""
"In the same way, you save yourself the trouble of opening your router's "
"ports and bypassing hairpinning."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "No micro DNS outages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:23
msgid ""
"If your Internet connection does not have a fixed public IP, you will be "
"forced to set up a dynamic domain name (Dynamic DNS). This solution may be "
"acceptable, but the DNS will only be updated at regular intervals (every two "
"minutes if it is a `noho.st` or `nohost.me` domain name). So there is a "
"chance that this will cause some display errors in the browser from time to "
"time, or even that another site will be displayed (the risks are however "
"reduced because the practice of self-hosting is not widespread)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:25
msgid ""
"With a neutral VPN, this problem is circumvented because the VPN can be "
"compared to a Virtual Internet connection, which has its own fixed IPv4 "
"address, so no need to update the domain name."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "The case of email"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:29
msgid ""
"Email is one of the most complex protocols to self-host, usually it is what "
"a user self-hosts last. Indeed, it is very easy to find yourself in a "
"situation where emails sent by the server are refused by the recipient SMTP "
"servers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:31
msgid "To avoid this you need to:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:36
msgid "configure the reverse DNS of the server's Internet connection (or VPN)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:36
msgid "a fixed IPv4"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:36
msgid ""
"that this IPv4 is removable from all blacklists (notably the IP must not be "
"on the DUL)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:36
msgid "to be able to open port 25 (as well as the other SMTP ports)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:38
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, none of the most common French ISPs respect all these points."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:40
msgid ""
"To overcome this, the use of a VPN respecting these points can be an "
"alternative."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:41
#, no-wrap
msgid "Trust"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:44
msgid ""
"Finally, if you do not want the content of your server's communications to "
"be spied on by equipment present on your ISP's network, you can use a VPN to "
"encrypt your communications and deport your trust to a VPN provider. "
"Remember, since 2015, the government officially deploys black boxes at the "
"large network operators whose objective is to tap all French digital "
"communications to preserve the scientific, economic and industrial interests "
"of France."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "Disadvantages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "Cost"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:50
msgid ""
"A neutral VPN has a cost since the operator who provides it must run a "
"server and use bandwidth. The prices of the FFDN's associative VPNs are "
"around 6 â‚¬ per month."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:51
#, no-wrap
msgid "Packet path"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:54
msgid ""
"When you set up a VPN on your server, if you don't set up any particular "
"configuration, the transfer of a file from a computer on the local network "
"to the server using the VPN, will go through the end of the VPN i.e. through "
"the server of the VPN provider."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:56
msgid "To solve this problem, there are two solutions:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:58
msgid ""
"transform the server into a router and connect the home equipments to it, "
"these equipments will then benefit from the VPN confidentiality too."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/10.providers/15.vpn/vpn_advantage.mdx:58
msgid ""
"use the YunoHost server as a DNS resolver when you are at home, in order to "
"redirect the server's domain names to the local IP rather than the public "
"IP. This operation can be done either on each equipment or on the router (if "
"the latter allows it)."
msgstr ""
